1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,320
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:20,600
From now on,
I'll devote even more of my love to you.

3
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:23,200
I'll also love you more and more.

4
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:25,680
At least we became
boyfriends at your house.

5
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:28,240
On top of that,
we also created new memories there.

6
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:33,560
<i>What I wanted was</i>

7
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:35,480
<i>a hug from my parents.</i>

8
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:39,800
It's time to stop holding
your younger self's hand and hold mine.

9
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:43,000
I'll be everything for you.

10
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:45,840
Walk with me, Qin.

11
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,360
Here you go.

12
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,640
Drink so you can feel refreshed.

13
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:10,760
Look at you drinking Ichitan.

14
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:11,720
You're adorable!

15
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:20,080
You're also adorable, Duang.

16
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,320
Adorable, my ass.

17
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:30,640
What are you looking at?

18
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:34,640
You're wearing my outfit today.
Let's do a fit check.

19
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:37,000
It's too early for this.

20
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:45,320
What's with that look?

21
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,960
I don't want you to overthink.

22
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:51,920
Overthink?

23
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,600
About last night?

24
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,600
Yes.

25
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:02,280
I'm done overthinking. There is
something else I need to think about.

26
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:06,160
Whoa…

27
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:08,520
You're right! The jazz showcase is today!

28
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,720
Are you nervous?

29
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,200
No.

30
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,240
Eat your food.

31
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:14,880
I'm not eating!

32
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:24,800
Okay, let's go.

33
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:25,920
Whoa! What?

34
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,000
I can walk.

35
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:30,560
- Hey.
- Huh?

36
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,160
Let's head out.

37
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:24,480
- It's looking pretty good.
- Yeah, it's a big event.

38
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:25,960
Whoa… What's the matter?

39
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:26,880
- Huh?
- In a hurry?

40
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:28,600
I'm buying roti for Qin. Want anything?

41
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:31,880
Absolutely. I'll have one with egg
and a lot of condensed milk.

42
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:33,320
A lot of condensed milk?

43
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:42,920
Jamie! I'd love to set
your messy system straight.

44
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,280
I'm dying to see what kind of person
you're falling in love with.

45
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,920
Stay out of it.

46
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,200
- Hey, I know…
- Whoa!

47
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,600
You're hiding something from me!

48
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,560
I'm sulking now.

49
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:56,400
Damn you!

50
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:05,160
Yes, baby?

51
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:08,560
<i>I don't think I'll have time to eat.</i>
<i>I have to be on standby.</i>

52
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,720
Okay, I'll be right with you.

53
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,400
I'm going to see Qin.
Find seats in front and call me.

54
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:18,840
What? Wait!

55
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:21,080
What about my roti with egg?

56
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:23,800
Jeez, what's with that dude?

57
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:25,480
He's out here selling my roti dreams.

58
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:28,840
I've never seen anyone so madly in love.

59
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:31,200
I'm mad.

60
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,280
<i>Good luck.</i>

61
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:41,240
<i>You can do it, my baby.</i>

62
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:07,960
What? Why did you take off your shirt?

63
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,840
I got hot.

64
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,920
Let's meet halfway then.

65
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,800
Were you trying to concentrate?

66
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,880
Are you nervous?

67
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:29,120
Now that you're here,
I don't feel nervous anymore.

68
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:32,240
Then…

69
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:34,160
Can you give me a smile?

70
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,400
Why here? It's a waste of film.

71
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,160
It's never a waste when it comes to you.

72
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:43,680
Let's take one together.

73
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:47,840
How about a selfie?

74
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:55,120
Three, two, one.

75
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:58,640
Wow.

76
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,560
Come on, Qin.

77
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:07,200
Let's get ready by the stage.

78
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,640
I won't say good luck
because you don't need it.

79
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,840
But I will say, "You can do it!"

80
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,520
Hold these for me.

81
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,080
Come on.

82
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,840
Right, Daung.

83
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:39,280
About what I said before,
I'm sorry I meddled.

84
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,600
It's fine.

85
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:43,280
I understand that
you wanted the event to go smoothly,

86
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,400
but…

87
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:47,240
I made Qin overthink that day.

88
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,760
But you did great earlier.

89
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:54,600
He might seem reserved,
but his heart was warmed by your support.

90
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:01,760
I'll be cheering.

91
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:16,320
- Hello?
<i>- I'm by the stage, on the right side.</i>

92
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,680
Alright, I'm coming.

93
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,120
TRUST GANGNAM CLINIC FOR HAIR REMOVAL

94
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,840
What a charming voice.

95
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:57,640
Shit!

96
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:59,240
The jazz students are on fire!

97
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:02,680
They're really going all out
with this year's event.

98
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,600
- Do you see that?
- What?

99
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:07,480
The art was done
by the Decorative Art students.

100
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,360
It looks awesome!

101
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,160
Well, it's the art students.

102
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,720
- How could it not be?
- Right on.

103
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,560
It's amazing. Sheesh!

104
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,840
Did you hear that?

105
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:18,840
More than clear.

106
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:21,440
They said that our artwork looks awesome.

107
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:23,840
- "Our," my ass!
- What?

108
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:25,000
You disappeared for days.

109
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:26,960
Well, I was the leader.

110
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:28,080
I was the leader!

111
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:29,240
- You were?
- Jeez!

112
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,280
If you were the leader,

113
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,760
I was your right hand man. Case closed.

114
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,240
- Shit…
- How fussy.

115
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,520
- Shit!
- What?!

116
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:37,960
Qin is up!

117
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,960
The stage looks awesome.

118
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,640
What's wrong?

119
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:44,280
He's so handsome it hurts.

120
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,560
How could someone

121
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:47,920
be so handsome,

122
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:48,920
talented,

123
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,280
and cool?

124
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:56,080
I already told you he's a ten!

125
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,640
Girl,

126
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,960
doesn't he look stressed out?

127
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:09,400
Maybe he's so serious
that he can't feel it.

128
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,200
Qin, you're gonna get in trouble.

129
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,560
Qin, baby!

130
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:17,600
Qin!

131
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:20,720
Qin, you're totally my type!

132
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:23,240
Damn, you're always so extra.

133
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,640
It's embarrassing.

134
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:32,040
Do you think… What the fuck is with you?

135
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:30,720
<i>If you look up at the sky one day</i>

136
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:37,880
<i>When the rain's coming</i>
<i>The clouds dress in gray</i>

137
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:42,600
<i>But you know, the clouds won't last…</i>

138
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:44,120
Damn,

139
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,000
that's some good music!

140
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,240
Leave me right here

141
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:52,160
'cause I just can't.

142
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:56,240
<i>Even if today</i>

143
00:11:56,320 --> 00:12:00,840
<i>Your dream's long to bloom</i>

144
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:06,400
<i>Be kind to yourself tonight</i>

145
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:11,360
<i>As long as you believe</i>

146
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:15,520
<i>That your hope stays close to you</i>

147
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:22,240
<i>Beautiful days come with time</i>

148
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:31,000
<i>Just smiling back at yourself once again</i>

149
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:37,880
<i>Smile through the storm and falling rain</i>

150
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:41,800
<i>Better days are waiting</i>

151
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:50,240
<i>Happiness will find you</i>

152
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:02,560
<i>It wasn't meant to be</i>

153
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,960
<i>Can't you see?</i>

154
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:13,440
<i>And I just had to leave</i>

155
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:19,440
<i>Now, I'm free</i>

156
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:27,200
<i>How could I think to myself</i>

157
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:31,360
<i>That you were the one for me?</i>

158
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:34,320
<i>I think we all agree</i>

159
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:41,120
<i>You're not my cup of tea</i>

160
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:09,880
<i>How could I think to myself</i>

161
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:14,320
<i>That you were the one for me?</i>

162
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:17,240
<i>I think we all agree</i>

163
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:23,120
<i>You're not my cup of tea</i>

164
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:27,880
<i>I think we all agree</i>

165
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:33,240
<i>You're not my cup of tea</i>

166
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:39,200
<i>I think we all agree</i>

167
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:58,040
<i>You're my cup of tea</i>

168
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:18,400
Whoa…

169
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:21,960
- Whoa…
- Got it?

170
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:24,800
Hello, Mr. Prachai.
Jettana here, live from the scene.

171
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:29,680
We're encountering a situation
where a student's heart skipped a beat.

172
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:31,560
Hey!

173
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:32,480
Hey…

174
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:39,800
I'd like to know something.
What makes your heart skip a beat?

175
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:42,040
It's my boyfriend.

176
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,480
"Boyfriend"!

177
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:47,760
I wish I could be all over him now.

178
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:55,920
From what you've heard,
how does it make you feel?

179
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,040
All the feels!

180
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,680
- But I won't ship them anymore.
- What?

181
00:15:58,760 --> 00:15:59,840
They are an item now!

182
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:08,000
May I ask where you are?

183
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,800
There's a flower delivery for you.

184
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:10,960
Hi.

185
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:12,080
Alright.

186
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:14,200
Here are the flowers.

187
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:16,120
May I take a photo?

188
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,120
Okay, thank you.

189
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,280
GOOD JOB, QIN
FROM DAD AND MOM

190
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,200
INCOMING CALL FROM MOM

191
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:31,840
Qin!

192
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:36,600
Let's head back.

193
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:38,560
Let me carry those.

194
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,360
Aw, this was really nice of your parents.

195
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:46,240
They never miss an event, huh?

196
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,560
They're busy.

197
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:51,680
Only their flowers can make it.

198
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:21,920
You must be so tired, my Qin.

199
00:17:22,599 --> 00:17:24,920
Do you want to eat something?
I'll order it for you.

200
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:38,400
You did an amazing job today.

201
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:43,480
When you sang,
the audience was really into it.

202
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:47,160
You really felt the song.

203
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:51,760
I couldn't take my eyes off you.

204
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:55,440
You seemed like
an entirely different person onstage

205
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:58,120
with how you held yourself.

206
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,440
I was clenching my fists so tightly.

207
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:02,520
How dramatic.

208
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:05,760
How was I even holding myself?

209
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:08,640
It's true.

210
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:10,800
Everyone was so impressed.

211
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:12,960
I'm getting kinda possessive.

212
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,640
But I do want everyone
to respect your skills.

213
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:22,000
When did you become so rational?

214
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:26,880
When I fell in love with you.

215
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,440
Here.

216
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,320
This is my gift for you.

217
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,040
I love you.

218
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:03,640
Thank you, Duang,

219
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:08,000
for always sticking by my side.

220
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:24,480
Are you sad?

221
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,640
Just tired.

222
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:32,320
You're tired?

223
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,240
Duang.

224
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,800
Sing for me.

225
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:53,840
You want me to sing for you?

226
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:58,400
Are you serious?

227
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:01,160
Come on.

228
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:14,880
<i>I want you by my side</i>

229
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:19,920
<i>Only you by my side</i>

230
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:23,040
<i>Nothing more</i>

231
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:29,320
<i>Nothing else I wish to adore</i>

232
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:33,600
<i>I want only you and me</i>

233
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:37,600
<i>Only us in my mind</i>

234
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:40,760
<i>Just us two</i>

235
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:48,640
<i>It's better than</i>
<i>Everything I've ever known</i>

236
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:52,880
That's beautiful.

237
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:14,640
<i>Did you receive the flowers we sent?</i>

238
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:18,840
<i>Sunflowers really suit you,</i>
<i>our smart cookie.</i>

239
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:57,080
Is everything okay?

240
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:13,680
Ever since I let go
of my younger self's hand to hold yours,

241
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:16,680
I've become more sensitive.

242
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:22,960
It's not a bad thing.

243
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:24,680
It's just new.

244
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:27,840
So…

245
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,520
what do you feel?

246
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:34,600
Lonely.

247
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:40,600
I mean,

248
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:43,120
all this time,

249
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:46,760
I've been so lonely.

250
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:51,120
You…

251
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,760
Don't.

252
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:54,440
Don't feel bad for me.

253
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:59,280
I just wanna say that

254
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,360
before I met you…

255
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:06,920
I was so lonely.

256
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:08,920
I was always lonely.

257
00:23:12,320 --> 00:23:13,800
It was like I had no one.

258
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:35,840
I'm okay now.

259
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:42,560
I am…

260
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,520
Hey…

261
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:54,880
Can I ask you for one thing?

262
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:04,080
Can you try telling your mom and dad

263
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,400
how you feel?

264
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:09,440
No.

265
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:11,960
I don't wanna talk to them.

266
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,080
Are you mad at them?

267
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:24,400
Yes.

268
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:26,520
And I'm scared…

269
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:29,800
that they won't listen.

270
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:33,800
All this time, they never listened to you?

271
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:43,040
Then…

272
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:45,120
Wanna play a game with me?

273
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:49,720
Send them a text.

274
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:52,360
Tell them you want them to come here,

275
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:55,120
and if they tell you that they're coming…

276
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:00,320
we'll talk to them.

277
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:01,520
I'm out.

278
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:06,760
You'll never know until you try.

279
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:11,040
You don't have to play the game with me.

280
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:15,960
But I do want you to ask yourself,
from the bottom of your heart,

281
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:17,920
what you want…

282
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:23,680
like how you trusted yourself earlier.

283
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:36,600
Papa, Mama…

284
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,720
<i>I want you and Dad to be here with me.</i>

285
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:14,040
<i>Can you come here?</i>

286
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,280
How are you feeling?

287
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:57,760
Can you tell me?

288
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:01,600
Scared.

289
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,280
Qin,

290
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,720
your Mom and Dad love you.

291
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:12,520
Or they wouldn't have
come back so quickly.

292
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:26,400
Come on.

293
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:38,200
- Hello, Mom, Dad.
- Hello there.

294
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:39,160
- Hi, Duang.
- Hello.

295
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:41,920
Look, I brought you lots of gifts.

296
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,640
Here are some snacks.

297
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:45,360
Let me take these.

298
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:46,640
- Here.
- Thank you.

299
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:48,120
- Thanks, Duang.
- You're welcome.

300
00:27:49,520 --> 00:27:50,440
Qin.

301
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:54,600
Wow…

302
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:56,720
Look,

303
00:27:57,440 --> 00:28:00,800
your place is crisp and clean.

304
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:02,960
That's my son.

305
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:04,120
Goodness, honey.

306
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:06,000
What are you worried about?

307
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:07,800
Qin is doing great living alone.

308
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:10,120
Right, Qin.

309
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:13,880
The jazz showcase is over, right?
I asked my secretary to send you flowers.

310
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:24,440
You said

311
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:26,720
you wanted us to come over.

312
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:28,120
Is everything okay?

313
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,160
Do you need something?

314
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:34,440
I'll buy it for you.

315
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:37,840
It's not like that.

316
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:40,240
- It's--
- I know.

317
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:44,920
You're mad at us for not attending
your jazz showcase, aren't you?

318
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:46,160
No.

319
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:51,760
Well, that's part of it.

320
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:54,440
But…

321
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:09,800
I do have something to tell you.

322
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:12,200
Sure.

323
00:29:12,280 --> 00:29:13,680
What is it?

324
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:19,600
I've never felt

325
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:21,640
like you were truly there for me.

326
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:23,680
Why…

327
00:29:26,040 --> 00:29:27,680
Why would you say that?

328
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:36,640
I've never forgotten

329
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:39,640
the memories of being abused.

330
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:46,400
I don't know if you know that,

331
00:29:46,480 --> 00:29:50,360
or if you are pretending to be clueless,
or are actually clueless.

332
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:51,800
Qin,

333
00:29:52,840 --> 00:29:53,760
about that…

334
00:29:54,520 --> 00:29:55,680
Mom and I talked about it.

335
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:58,400
- Right.
- It was over,

336
00:29:58,480 --> 00:30:00,480
so we decided not to bring it up again.

337
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:01,760
What did you talk about?

338
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,760
What did you two talk about?

339
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:17,520
Please.

340
00:30:19,040 --> 00:30:21,600
Can I, for once, be a part of this family?

341
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:29,160
Well…

342
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:33,080
Mom and I

343
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:35,040
were worried that

344
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:38,920
you'd struggle
with what happened back then.

345
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:44,560
As time went on, we…

346
00:30:44,640 --> 00:30:46,360
- always watched over you.
- Yes.

347
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:48,680
We saw that

348
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:51,280
you overcame it with grace.

349
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:52,600
Yes.

350
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:55,480
You're always such a good boy.

351
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:56,680
I thought that…

352
00:30:57,600 --> 00:30:59,840
if you ever wanted anything,
like this condo,

353
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:01,680
we would buy it for you.

354
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:03,520
Whatever you wished for.

355
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:06,600
When you wanted a tutor
or wanted to go to university,

356
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:08,160
we always supported you.

357
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,440
Okay.

358
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:16,560
I understand.

359
00:31:20,800 --> 00:31:22,120
Qin.

360
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:24,360
- We--
- Yeah…

361
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:26,600
Everything you gave me,
including this condo

362
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:27,520
and my education…

363
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:28,680
- Well, Dad--
- Yeah…

364
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:30,080
- Mom and I--
- He and I…

365
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:31,280
- We tried.
- We really did.

366
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:32,600
What about me?

367
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:35,120
What about what I actually want?

368
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:37,960
I…

369
00:31:38,040 --> 00:31:39,680
The reason we did all this

370
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:41,280
is because we love you.

371
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:44,600
Mom, you don't get it at all.
You never even tried to.

372
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:45,600
Qin…

373
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:49,080
What's happening, Son?

374
00:31:49,880 --> 00:31:52,480
You've never been like this.
You were always a good boy. You…

375
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:54,560
You were always so capable, I…

376
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:57,000
We barely ever needed to worry about you.

377
00:31:57,080 --> 00:31:58,880
Being good at everything

378
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:02,080
is the reason you're never there, huh?

379
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:07,160
Then I don't want to be good.
I'd rather not be good.

380
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:08,160
Qin…

381
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:12,080
what you're saying,
I think you're being unreasonable.

382
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,760
- Mom, I'm not being unreasonable.
- Qin, stop.

383
00:32:14,840 --> 00:32:17,640
Listen to your mother.
We've done our best raising you.

384
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:20,120
We've put our heart and soul
into caring for you.

385
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:22,680
Are you really
gonna pay us back by being snarky?

386
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:26,440
If you're upset about us
not going to your showcase,

387
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:27,600
just say it.

388
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:29,720
Right, just tell us.

389
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:31,920
That's why you're upset, isn't it?

390
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:33,960
<i>- Even when I'm gone…</i>
- Say it, Qin.

391
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:35,840
<i>…you won't get to be with your parents!</i>

392
00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:37,760
- Say it out loud!
- Stop!

393
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:44,480
Don't you realize
why I turned out like this?

394
00:32:44,560 --> 00:32:46,240
It's because of you guys!

395
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:50,680
Qin,

396
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:53,720
I won't accept you
talking to us like this.

397
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:55,640
- Apologize to us.
- No.

398
00:32:56,360 --> 00:32:57,320
Qin!

399
00:32:57,400 --> 00:33:00,000
You're making me feel bad,
do you know that?

400
00:33:00,080 --> 00:33:01,080
I don't!

401
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:03,520
Because you've never told me anything.

402
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:05,880
- All you do is leave me alone!
- Qin!

403
00:33:07,440 --> 00:33:08,360
What?

404
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:09,960
Are you angry?

405
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:13,120
Am I not a good kid anymore?

406
00:33:16,760 --> 00:33:20,400
All this time, I followed the path
you said was nothing but great.

407
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:24,160
I just wanted you to ask if I'm tired.

408
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:27,040
You know?

409
00:33:27,120 --> 00:33:30,680
Even now, what happened when I was a child
still haunts me.

410
00:33:32,400 --> 00:33:34,080
When I was abused,

411
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:36,280
I cried out for you guys,
but no one answered.

412
00:33:36,360 --> 00:33:37,560
Why didn't you say anything?

413
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:40,240
Do you ever listen when I do?

414
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:42,320
You're not even listening to me now!

415
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:45,520
Do you know how uncomfortable it is
to be in this family?

416
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:46,760
Okay.

417
00:33:46,840 --> 00:33:47,680
Qin,

418
00:33:48,840 --> 00:33:49,760
it's my fault.

419
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,840
Alright? It's all my fault.

420
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:57,680
If this is what you want, fine.
I'll take all the blame.

421
00:33:57,760 --> 00:34:00,640
It's my fault. Are you satisfied? Are you?

422
00:34:15,199 --> 00:34:16,600
Duang, I can't take it…

423
00:34:24,280 --> 00:34:25,480
It's fine.

424
00:34:29,679 --> 00:34:31,199
I'm right here with you.

425
00:34:31,760 --> 00:34:33,560
I'm right here.

426
00:34:34,639 --> 00:34:36,239
This is all it takes, Mom.

427
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:39,800
This is all it takes to fix everything.

428
00:34:39,880 --> 00:34:41,880
Just hug him.

429
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:45,000
That's all it takes.

430
00:34:53,560 --> 00:34:55,400
You're not going to stop? Stop!

431
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:11,200
Papa, Mama…

432
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:32,000
<i>- Cry all you want!</i>
- Qin…

433
00:35:32,080 --> 00:35:33,280
<i>Cry here, outside the house.</i>

434
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:34,280
Qin…

435
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:37,800
<i>Are you going to stop?!</i>

436
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:41,480
<i>You're not going to stop?</i>

437
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:47,320
- Dad, Mom.
<i>- Are you going to stop?!</i>

438
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:48,680
I'm so sorry, Son.

439
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:52,560
I'm hurt.

440
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:56,440
Please stay with me.

441
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:00,640
I don't want to eat mud anymore.

442
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:04,800
I don't want to.

443
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:05,960
I'm sorry.

444
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:09,520
- Please don't leave me.
- Sure, Son.

445
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:11,600
- Can you please not leave me?
- Alright, Son.

446
00:36:11,680 --> 00:36:13,080
We're right here.

447
00:36:13,160 --> 00:36:14,120
I'm sorry.

448
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:15,360
Are you going to stay?

449
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:17,400
- We are.
- We're not leaving you, Qin.

450
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,360
I'm sorry.

451
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,400
Then…

452
00:36:34,120 --> 00:36:35,560
from now on,

453
00:36:36,280 --> 00:36:38,400
just focus on becoming our boy again.

454
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:40,960
Alright?

455
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:45,160
Let's be a not-so-capable family together.

456
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:47,920
We'll talk about everything.

457
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:51,520
If there's a problem,
we'll work on it together.

458
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:00,680
You too, Duang.

459
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:03,880
Alright.

460
00:37:04,600 --> 00:37:05,480
How does this sound?

461
00:37:06,080 --> 00:37:07,000
It's adorable.

462
00:37:09,560 --> 00:37:11,160
I'm heading out now, Qin.

463
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:12,080
Okay.

464
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:16,800
Take care, Son.

465
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:18,280
You guys too.

466
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:19,880
Bye-bye.

467
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:22,160
- See you, Duang.
- Bye.

468
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:23,240
Bye-bye.

469
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:27,200
- Let's go, honey.
- Let's go.

470
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:29,400
Get home safe.

471
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:38,000
Yay!

472
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:48,280
Your parents were right.

473
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:50,840
You really are an amazing boy.

474
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:53,440
You finally got through it,

475
00:37:54,080 --> 00:37:55,120
my Qin.

476
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:45,320
Come on…

477
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:47,400
Come on…

478
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:48,400
Come on…

479
00:39:07,720 --> 00:39:09,840
What's your deal? Why so clingy?

480
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:16,600
You're at ease now, aren't you?

481
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:23,800
Seeing you happy with your mom and dad

482
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:26,640
makes me happy too.

483
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:29,320
Not yet.

484
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:31,920
That feeling is still lingering.

485
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:35,000
Things like this take time.

486
00:39:36,520 --> 00:39:38,200
But it's a good start.

487
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:42,400
At least I got to hug them.

488
00:39:43,160 --> 00:39:44,320
This time around,

489
00:39:44,400 --> 00:39:47,280
I really felt like Mom and Dad were there.

490
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:06,560
Duang.

491
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,360
Thank you.

492
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,680
No need for that.

493
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:17,880
I'm happy to help.

494
00:40:40,280 --> 00:40:43,600
Wanna go to Siam after exams?
I wanna get the film developed.

495
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:45,480
After that, we'll go home.

496
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:48,040
I…

497
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:50,040
will do whatever you say.

498
00:41:11,640 --> 00:41:12,880
Sweet dreams, Duang.

499
00:41:17,760 --> 00:41:18,680
Sweet dreams.

500
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:33,680
Duang?

501
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:38,360
Thank you for today.

502
00:41:40,640 --> 00:41:42,360
Thank you for today too.

503
00:42:01,040 --> 00:42:01,920
Go on.

504
00:42:17,240 --> 00:42:18,800
Hi, I'm here to develop this film.

505
00:42:21,200 --> 00:42:24,000
It'll take about 30 minutes.

506
00:42:24,080 --> 00:42:24,920
Okay.

507
00:42:26,640 --> 00:42:27,520
Here's the receipt.

508
00:42:27,600 --> 00:42:28,920
Thank you.

509
00:42:33,720 --> 00:42:34,920
Buying a new camera?

510
00:42:38,440 --> 00:42:39,320
I'm not.

511
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:40,280
Just browsing.

512
00:42:41,720 --> 00:42:43,520
Do you think the photos will be beautiful?

513
00:42:43,600 --> 00:42:45,280
Of course, we're pros.

514
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:46,400
But you,

515
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:48,520
you are the most beautiful.

516
00:42:54,520 --> 00:42:57,080
Wanna go for a walk?
We can come back later.

517
00:44:24,320 --> 00:44:25,360
Qin.

518
00:44:26,280 --> 00:44:27,800
Let's change our outfits.

519
00:44:40,520 --> 00:44:41,600
I'll go with this.

520
00:44:45,200 --> 00:44:47,200
That won't do!

521
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:50,720
Then, can you wear a tank top inside?

522
00:45:22,800 --> 00:45:25,080
I've changed my mind. Not this one.

523
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:32,120
Don't rush to say I'm not a hottie.

524
00:45:32,200 --> 00:45:34,240
Give me a chance to dress up first.

525
00:45:34,320 --> 00:45:37,320
If you see me when I'm not mewing,
I'm gonna look skibidi.

526
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:38,920
Speak properly.

527
00:45:39,440 --> 00:45:40,840
What?

528
00:45:40,920 --> 00:45:42,200
Why though?

529
00:45:42,280 --> 00:45:44,160
I think I look fine in this.

530
00:45:44,240 --> 00:45:45,680
Plus, it's not expensive.

531
00:45:46,320 --> 00:45:48,760
- It is.
- Whoa…

532
00:45:48,840 --> 00:45:50,760
Said the boy
who wears shoes worth 30,000 baht.

533
00:45:50,840 --> 00:45:52,480
A bit rich coming from you.

534
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:56,480
Said the boy
who bought a camera worth 55,000 baht

535
00:45:56,560 --> 00:45:58,080
and ended up having no money to eat?

536
00:45:58,520 --> 00:45:59,440
A bit rich, no?

537
00:46:00,960 --> 00:46:01,880
Then…

538
00:46:02,600 --> 00:46:04,120
give me a reason.

539
00:46:04,200 --> 00:46:06,240
If it sounds reasonable, I won't buy it.

540
00:46:10,880 --> 00:46:11,880
Why?

541
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:14,320
I look good in darker colors, don't I?

542
00:46:14,400 --> 00:46:15,920
Just buy it, then.

543
00:46:17,240 --> 00:46:18,880
Just say you're possessive.

544
00:46:28,120 --> 00:46:29,040
How about

545
00:46:30,200 --> 00:46:31,160
you try this one?

546
00:47:09,520 --> 00:47:11,240
How is it? Does it look okay?

547
00:47:14,720 --> 00:47:18,040
There's one word I want to say,
but you won't like it.

548
00:47:19,240 --> 00:47:20,440
Don't say it then.

549
00:47:58,800 --> 00:48:00,560
Do you think people outside will know

550
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:02,840
I'm teasing you?

551
00:48:06,920 --> 00:48:07,920
Bastard.

552
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:29,640
Your heart is beating out of your chest.

553
00:48:31,960 --> 00:48:33,720
Now you're the one

554
00:48:34,320 --> 00:48:35,480
being teased.

555
00:48:55,760 --> 00:48:56,600
Enough.

556
00:48:58,760 --> 00:48:59,680
It's hot.

557
00:49:00,200 --> 00:49:02,480
I wanna take you home right now.

558
00:49:03,760 --> 00:49:05,040
In your dreams.

559
00:49:05,120 --> 00:49:06,200
Go pay.

560
00:49:17,920 --> 00:49:19,520
I got everything I need.

561
00:49:24,400 --> 00:49:25,400
What?

562
00:49:26,800 --> 00:49:28,520
I want to invite you over for a meal.

563
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:30,400
Do you wanna come?

564
00:49:30,480 --> 00:49:31,960
Where is this coming from?

565
00:49:32,480 --> 00:49:35,200
Well, when I was shopping earlier,

566
00:49:35,280 --> 00:49:37,520
I realized
I haven't introduced you to my parents.

567
00:49:38,560 --> 00:49:39,960
What are you introducing me as?

568
00:49:41,160 --> 00:49:42,280
I'll tell them that

569
00:49:42,360 --> 00:49:43,560
you're my boyfriend.

570
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:46,240
Is that a good idea?

571
00:49:48,520 --> 00:49:50,560
My parents are really nice.

572
00:49:50,640 --> 00:49:52,280
My mom is also good at making desserts.

573
00:49:55,560 --> 00:49:56,400
Please come.

574
00:49:58,200 --> 00:49:59,040
I don't mind.

575
00:49:59,120 --> 00:50:01,280
- I'll go.
- Then…

576
00:50:01,360 --> 00:50:04,440
Let's go see your mom and dad today,
and we'll visit my house later.

577
00:50:06,240 --> 00:50:07,080
Let's go.

578
00:50:12,400 --> 00:50:14,200
Hey, let's take a photo.

579
00:50:24,520 --> 00:50:26,760
You're so cute. What do you want, baby?

580
00:50:29,600 --> 00:50:30,960
Duang.

581
00:50:43,160 --> 00:50:44,760
Here you go.

582
00:50:44,840 --> 00:50:46,320
- Here's yours, sweetie.
- Thanks.

583
00:50:46,400 --> 00:50:47,800
- For you two.
- Popcorn!

584
00:50:47,880 --> 00:50:49,560
- Thank you, Mom.
- Thank you.

585
00:50:50,480 --> 00:50:52,120
- Where were we?
- Oh, right.

586
00:50:52,640 --> 00:50:55,840
How about we start it over
so Mom can catch up too?

587
00:50:55,920 --> 00:50:57,400
Sure.

588
00:50:58,160 --> 00:50:59,120
Of course.

589
00:50:59,200 --> 00:51:01,560
Actually, I got lost with the subtitles.

590
00:51:03,440 --> 00:51:04,560
Alright, let's start over.

591
00:51:04,640 --> 00:51:07,880
Okay! It's so nice
to watch a movie with Qin.

592
00:51:12,200 --> 00:51:13,120
Dad, Mom,

593
00:51:13,760 --> 00:51:16,880
I have… something to tell you.

594
00:51:18,600 --> 00:51:19,760
What is it, Son?

595
00:51:24,240 --> 00:51:26,200
Duang and I…

596
00:51:30,920 --> 00:51:32,200
are boyfriends.

597
00:51:37,040 --> 00:51:38,120
Dad and I…

598
00:51:46,760 --> 00:51:49,280
Dad and I already knew.

599
00:51:50,880 --> 00:51:52,560
I'm so happy.

600
00:51:53,440 --> 00:51:55,720
Duang, come give Mom a hug.

601
00:51:59,240 --> 00:52:00,400
So…

602
00:52:01,280 --> 00:52:03,360
I need to get serious.

603
00:52:07,800 --> 00:52:09,560
Welcome to the family, Duang.

604
00:52:09,640 --> 00:52:12,760
Yay!

605
00:52:12,840 --> 00:52:15,560
- Yay!
- Yay!

606
00:52:15,640 --> 00:52:17,960
Okay, I think
we'll need to start over again.

607
00:52:18,040 --> 00:52:19,440
That's right.

608
00:52:19,520 --> 00:52:21,240
I'll try keep up with the subtitles.

609
00:52:21,320 --> 00:52:22,320
Get 'em, Duang.

610
00:52:22,400 --> 00:52:24,080
- Sure thing.
- Ready?

611
00:52:25,120 --> 00:52:26,000
Let's go.

612
00:52:38,240 --> 00:52:40,480
Baby, come sit on my lap.

613
00:52:49,840 --> 00:52:51,040
Are you tired today?

614
00:52:54,280 --> 00:52:56,360
When you told your parents,

615
00:52:56,440 --> 00:52:57,680
I was flabbergasted.

616
00:52:57,760 --> 00:52:59,040
You really went all out.

617
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:02,520
It gave me peace of mind. How about you?

618
00:53:04,120 --> 00:53:06,240
I'm happy. I wanna eat you up!

619
00:53:10,800 --> 00:53:12,080
You're so annoying.

620
00:53:13,120 --> 00:53:16,640
I want to thank you a million times more
for choosing me.

621
00:53:17,160 --> 00:53:18,040
Stop.

622
00:53:26,320 --> 00:53:27,400
Didn't you see something?

623
00:53:28,640 --> 00:53:29,760
See what?

624
00:53:31,480 --> 00:53:34,360
When you were lifting stuff,
did you see anything?

625
00:53:37,280 --> 00:53:38,600
What?

626
00:53:42,320 --> 00:53:44,800
Is it… the ghost in your room?

627
00:53:46,200 --> 00:53:47,360
I see dead people!

628
00:54:02,200 --> 00:54:03,840
Is it the ghost in your room?

629
00:54:16,600 --> 00:54:18,480
Why are you scared? Here.

630
00:54:18,960 --> 00:54:20,640
Whoa, you!

631
00:54:21,120 --> 00:54:21,960
Whoa…

632
00:54:22,800 --> 00:54:24,040
My heart almost stopped.

633
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:27,520
I'm so happy.

634
00:54:35,000 --> 00:54:36,880
I put a lot of thought into this.

635
00:54:39,840 --> 00:54:40,920
Thank you.

636
00:54:41,960 --> 00:54:43,800
You did this for me?

637
00:54:50,040 --> 00:54:50,920
Let me see.

638
00:54:55,640 --> 00:54:57,120
Wow…

639
00:55:07,920 --> 00:55:09,200
Whoa, Qin!

640
00:55:09,280 --> 00:55:10,880
These are nice.

641
00:55:10,960 --> 00:55:12,000
I love them.

642
00:55:18,760 --> 00:55:22,080
But you shouldn't have.
They're really expensive.

643
00:55:22,160 --> 00:55:23,880
Are you sure about this?

644
00:55:24,840 --> 00:55:26,040
You fussed about the camera.

645
00:55:27,880 --> 00:55:30,360
That's why I debated giving them to you.

646
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:32,920
But after some pondering,

647
00:55:33,520 --> 00:55:36,600
since I genuinely wanted to,
I decided to buy them.

648
00:55:37,680 --> 00:55:39,320
Plus, I'm not struggling.

649
00:55:41,200 --> 00:55:42,560
I know they're expensive…

650
00:55:45,400 --> 00:55:46,600
but they suit you.

651
00:55:49,960 --> 00:55:51,080
I love you, Qin.

652
00:55:54,240 --> 00:55:55,560
I love you too, Duang.

653
00:56:06,840 --> 00:56:07,920
Here you go.

654
00:56:14,600 --> 00:56:18,280
I'M IN A GOOD MOOD TODAY
MY BOYFRIEND PICKED MY OUTFIT

655
00:56:27,760 --> 00:56:30,040
<i>Is this a makeover or a renovation?</i>

656
00:56:30,960 --> 00:56:33,160
<i>Jettana, just say you're jelly.</i>

657
00:56:36,680 --> 00:56:39,360
<i>Who'd be jealous</i>
<i>of a lover boy showing off his love?</i>

658
00:56:40,640 --> 00:56:42,200
<i>When will it be your turn?</i>

659
00:56:42,280 --> 00:56:44,600
<i>Is hooking up</i>
<i>all you'll ever look for in life?</i>

660
00:56:50,720 --> 00:56:52,160
Are you making your own clothes?

661
00:56:54,480 --> 00:56:55,880
It's for you.

662
00:56:56,640 --> 00:56:58,120
Try it on for me.

663
00:56:58,200 --> 00:57:00,080
What made you want to do that?

664
00:57:01,720 --> 00:57:04,800
We've spent so much time together
that I know the size you wear.

665
00:57:06,160 --> 00:57:07,800
Get up.

666
00:57:12,800 --> 00:57:13,920
Here.

667
00:57:19,040 --> 00:57:20,480
Hold up.

668
00:57:21,760 --> 00:57:23,880
Go change properly, not here.

669
00:57:23,960 --> 00:57:25,440
What?

670
00:57:25,520 --> 00:57:26,800
Why not?

671
00:57:26,880 --> 00:57:28,320
It's nothing you haven't seen.

672
00:57:32,280 --> 00:57:34,920
Alright. I'll go change in the bathroom.

673
00:57:51,040 --> 00:57:52,520
Here I am.

674
00:57:56,480 --> 00:57:58,160
That looks sharp. It really suits you.

675
00:58:05,600 --> 00:58:06,600
Try this one on for me.

676
00:58:10,840 --> 00:58:12,040
Overalls?

677
00:58:18,800 --> 00:58:20,000
Please?

678
00:58:21,960 --> 00:58:24,160
Will they look good on me?

679
00:58:24,800 --> 00:58:28,000
Of course. You have a nice body.
Everything looks good on you.

680
00:58:30,720 --> 00:58:33,160
I really like your eyes
when you get serious.

681
00:58:34,200 --> 00:58:35,400
Then…

682
00:58:36,440 --> 00:58:38,760
Would you be a model for my final project?

683
00:58:39,520 --> 00:58:41,240
If I agree to being your model,

684
00:58:41,840 --> 00:58:43,040
what do I get?

685
00:58:43,960 --> 00:58:45,440
Well, what do you want?

686
00:58:50,400 --> 00:58:52,720
You know too well what I want.

687
00:58:55,400 --> 00:58:57,720
Are you sure this is all you want?

688
00:59:23,440 --> 00:59:24,680
I'm not falling in love.

689
00:59:25,280 --> 00:59:26,120
Marvis…

690
00:59:39,880 --> 00:59:40,880
Huh?

691
00:59:41,920 --> 00:59:43,280
I'm not good with words.

692
00:59:43,360 --> 00:59:45,440
I know.

693
00:59:46,720 --> 00:59:48,200
Will it be okay?

694
00:59:49,120 --> 00:59:50,600
It'll be completely fine.

695
00:59:51,280 --> 00:59:53,520
If you don't want to talk, I will.

696
00:59:58,160 --> 01:00:00,680
Everyone in my family is talkative.

697
01:00:01,480 --> 01:00:03,680
My parents are
even more talkative than I am.

698
01:00:03,760 --> 01:00:05,640
Don't you worry.

699
01:00:05,720 --> 01:00:07,560
I'll never leave your side.

700
01:00:08,080 --> 01:00:12,000
Besides, you're good
at having conversations with me.

701
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:16,280
Thank you.

702
01:00:18,800 --> 01:00:19,920
What for?

703
01:00:21,760 --> 01:00:25,160
Thank you
for making me a better version of myself.

704
01:00:28,840 --> 01:00:30,680
I also thank you

705
01:00:30,760 --> 01:00:32,680
for making me

706
01:00:32,760 --> 01:00:34,680
a better version of myself.

707
01:00:48,240 --> 01:00:49,160
Come on.

708
01:00:50,560 --> 01:00:52,600
I'll hold your hand through all of it!

709
01:00:57,720 --> 01:00:59,560
Hey, I can't get out that way.

710
01:01:05,520 --> 01:01:07,800
Did you transfer him the money?

711
01:01:07,880 --> 01:01:09,880
Darling! Duang is home!

712
01:01:09,960 --> 01:01:12,480
Jeez, like no one can tell
you miss your son.

713
01:01:12,560 --> 01:01:14,560
You… Duang!

714
01:01:15,120 --> 01:01:16,040
Duang!

715
01:01:16,120 --> 01:01:19,520
I'm home!

716
01:01:19,600 --> 01:01:21,880
Hello, Dad. Hello, Mom.

717
01:01:21,960 --> 01:01:24,320
Hi, there. Come here, Duang.

718
01:01:24,440 --> 01:01:27,880
Give Mom a hug. I've missed you!

719
01:01:30,160 --> 01:01:31,120
Funan, hi.

720
01:01:31,200 --> 01:01:32,360
Hey.

721
01:01:33,520 --> 01:01:36,920
Look at your brother for once,
not just your phone!

722
01:01:37,000 --> 01:01:38,080
Bro, look over there.

723
01:01:38,160 --> 01:01:40,680
Look at Dad and Mom.
They miss you like crazy.

724
01:01:40,760 --> 01:01:43,120
It wouldn't feel right
if these two didn't fight.

725
01:01:43,200 --> 01:01:45,120
Stop right here, guys.

726
01:01:45,640 --> 01:01:47,560
I've brought someone special home.

727
01:01:49,480 --> 01:01:50,360
This is Qin!

728
01:01:53,080 --> 01:01:54,160
Too soon!

729
01:01:54,800 --> 01:01:55,840
I'm just so excited!

730
01:01:55,920 --> 01:01:56,960
He's my boyfriend.

731
01:01:57,040 --> 01:01:59,000
- He is… my boyfriend.
- So cute.

732
01:02:00,920 --> 01:02:01,960
He's adorable.

733
01:02:03,280 --> 01:02:04,280
Qin…

734
01:02:04,360 --> 01:02:05,920
- Hello, Mom.
- Hi, sweetie.

735
01:02:06,000 --> 01:02:06,960
Hello, Dad.

736
01:02:07,040 --> 01:02:08,720
- Hello, Funan.
- Hi.

737
01:02:09,920 --> 01:02:10,760
Dad,

738
01:02:11,520 --> 01:02:13,280
Duang really did it!

739
01:02:13,360 --> 01:02:16,720
Right? I thought this day
would never come.

740
01:02:16,800 --> 01:02:18,840
Hey, don't make fun of your son!

741
01:02:18,920 --> 01:02:20,920
Duang is my son. Of course he did it.

742
01:02:21,720 --> 01:02:23,760
Mom, you're buttering me up.

743
01:02:23,840 --> 01:02:25,560
But let me tell you guys that

744
01:02:25,640 --> 01:02:27,480
Qin isn't good with words.

745
01:02:27,560 --> 01:02:29,080
Please be patient with him.

746
01:02:29,160 --> 01:02:31,720
That's fine. Make yourself at home, Qin.

747
01:02:31,800 --> 01:02:35,360
Every animal here has been vaccinated,
so make yourself comfortable.

748
01:02:35,440 --> 01:02:36,400
We're not animals.

749
01:02:37,480 --> 01:02:38,800
Alright.

750
01:02:45,680 --> 01:02:48,400
Qin! My… you're so cute.

751
01:02:48,480 --> 01:02:49,840
What a cute one.

752
01:02:49,920 --> 01:02:51,280
You're really handsome too.

753
01:02:51,360 --> 01:02:52,960
Exactly as Duang described.

754
01:02:53,040 --> 01:02:54,360
True, Mom.

755
01:02:54,440 --> 01:02:57,320
He's the CEO of being adorable!

756
01:02:57,400 --> 01:02:58,840
Right. Hey, Qin.

757
01:02:59,880 --> 01:03:02,360
Have you ever tried Betong chicken?

758
01:03:03,120 --> 01:03:04,440
- Jeez, Dad.
- Not now.

759
01:03:04,520 --> 01:03:05,880
Is this how you're treating him?

760
01:03:05,960 --> 01:03:06,840
Right? I'm confused.

761
01:03:06,920 --> 01:03:07,920
Come on now.

762
01:03:08,000 --> 01:03:10,920
I haven't, but I have seen pictures.

763
01:03:11,000 --> 01:03:12,800
Right, it's okay if you haven't.

764
01:03:12,880 --> 01:03:14,880
But is there something else you like?

765
01:03:14,960 --> 01:03:17,560
Duang said you have many favorites,
like desserts and all that.

766
01:03:17,640 --> 01:03:19,960
- Yes, I like everything.
- Right.

767
01:03:20,040 --> 01:03:22,280
Would you like to come
to the kitchen with me,

768
01:03:22,360 --> 01:03:24,080
or would you prefer waiting out here?

769
01:03:24,160 --> 01:03:25,240
I'll…

770
01:03:25,320 --> 01:03:27,840
Mom, you're luring him with food.

771
01:03:27,920 --> 01:03:30,080
I'm not. I've just prepared a lot of food,

772
01:03:30,160 --> 01:03:32,720
so I want him
to check it out in the kitchen.

773
01:03:32,800 --> 01:03:34,640
- Wanna come with?
- Sure. I'll go with you.

774
01:03:34,720 --> 01:03:37,080
Qin, are the dining room
and kitchen the same?

775
01:03:37,160 --> 01:03:38,160
Mom's confused.

776
01:03:38,240 --> 01:03:39,640
But I do think they might be.

777
01:03:39,720 --> 01:03:41,000
Qin, walk with me.

778
01:03:42,240 --> 01:03:43,640
- Duang.
- Yes?

779
01:03:43,720 --> 01:03:45,120
Come help me set the table.

780
01:03:45,200 --> 01:03:46,360
What about Funan?

781
01:03:47,680 --> 01:03:49,960
Whoa, don't point your finger at me.

782
01:03:50,040 --> 01:03:51,400
Shoo, go help Dad.

783
01:03:51,480 --> 01:03:54,800
Stop it. Both of you, come on.
Let's help each other.

784
01:03:54,880 --> 01:03:56,040
Come on, I'm hungry.

785
01:03:58,560 --> 01:03:59,480
Whoa!

786
01:04:01,920 --> 01:04:03,600
- Qin?
- Yes?

787
01:04:03,680 --> 01:04:05,800
What specific desserts do you like?

788
01:04:07,080 --> 01:04:08,320
Nothing specific.

789
01:04:08,840 --> 01:04:10,640
I love every dessert out there.

790
01:04:10,720 --> 01:04:14,640
Nice, you're not picky.
This family doesn't care for desserts.

791
01:04:14,720 --> 01:04:19,760
I even took some cooking classes
and never got to show off my skills, Qin.

792
01:04:19,840 --> 01:04:21,760
What level of sweetness do you like?

793
01:04:21,840 --> 01:04:23,800
- Just normal sweetness.
- That's right.

794
01:04:23,880 --> 01:04:26,920
That's exactly how it should be. Here.

795
01:04:27,000 --> 01:04:30,720
I'll teach you how to make jelly.
How does that sound? It's not hard.

796
01:04:30,800 --> 01:04:33,560
It'll only take a sec,
and maybe three or four stories.

797
01:04:33,640 --> 01:04:35,880
- Okay.
- We'll start by turning on the stove.

798
01:04:35,960 --> 01:04:39,040
Then you place the pot on it.
It's so simple.

799
01:04:39,120 --> 01:04:40,040
See?

800
01:04:40,120 --> 01:04:44,040
But you can relax
because if it's edible, we'll eat it.

801
01:04:44,120 --> 01:04:46,040
If not, we'll throw it away.

802
01:04:46,120 --> 01:04:47,880
I know who Duang takes after.

803
01:04:48,840 --> 01:04:51,800
Is it me? I need to tell you this then.
Wanna listen?

804
01:04:51,880 --> 01:04:52,960
I do, Mom.

805
01:04:53,040 --> 01:04:54,720
Right! Let's sit down.

806
01:04:56,040 --> 01:04:58,520
It's story time. When Duang was little,

807
01:04:58,600 --> 01:05:02,320
when I took him places,
everyone said we were like two peas--

808
01:05:05,360 --> 01:05:06,280
Eavesdropping, I see.

809
01:05:06,360 --> 01:05:08,280
Everyone said we were the same.

810
01:05:08,360 --> 01:05:10,320
- Right.
- I was so confused.

811
01:05:10,400 --> 01:05:13,720
Eavesdropping to see
if he gets along well with Mom?

812
01:05:13,800 --> 01:05:16,280
Aw, you puppy!

813
01:05:16,360 --> 01:05:17,800
I'm so happy

814
01:05:18,560 --> 01:05:20,440
that Qin gets along with our family.

815
01:05:24,920 --> 01:05:28,440
- Funan, I have a question.
- What?

816
01:05:29,720 --> 01:05:30,920
Do you think…

817
01:05:31,000 --> 01:05:32,920
Dad and Mom are okay with Qin?

818
01:05:33,760 --> 01:05:34,760
Look at them.

819
01:05:35,600 --> 01:05:37,040
They're besties already.

820
01:05:37,120 --> 01:05:40,240
Qin, you sing so beautifully!
Did you take singing classes?

821
01:05:40,320 --> 01:05:42,120
Mom is kind.

822
01:05:42,200 --> 01:05:43,160
As for Dad,

823
01:05:43,240 --> 01:05:46,480
even though he's a poser, he's also nice.

824
01:05:46,560 --> 01:05:47,800
- I'm telling Dad.
- Whoa!

825
01:05:48,720 --> 01:05:50,200
Why did you ask?

826
01:05:52,000 --> 01:05:56,080
I'm scared Qin will feel uncomfortable.
Our family isn't like his.

827
01:05:56,760 --> 01:05:58,360
Before you overthink,

828
01:05:58,440 --> 01:06:00,960
have you asked him if he's uncomfortable?

829
01:06:02,880 --> 01:06:03,920
Exactly.

830
01:06:04,000 --> 01:06:05,560
So don't think for him.

831
01:06:05,640 --> 01:06:08,880
When you're in a relationship,
you can't think for each other.

832
01:06:08,960 --> 01:06:10,080
You need to talk.

833
01:06:11,200 --> 01:06:12,480
I'm scared he won't like us.

834
01:06:12,560 --> 01:06:13,800
Jeez.

835
01:06:13,880 --> 01:06:15,040
If he doesn't,

836
01:06:15,120 --> 01:06:16,640
he should tell you

837
01:06:16,720 --> 01:06:19,760
because that means
you have to adapt to each other.

838
01:06:19,840 --> 01:06:22,240
Even family members
can't think for each other.

839
01:06:22,840 --> 01:06:26,960
So… you need to talk to each other
so you know what the other is thinking.

840
01:06:28,080 --> 01:06:29,680
Especially in a relationship

841
01:06:29,760 --> 01:06:32,280
where you grew up
in different environments.

842
01:06:32,800 --> 01:06:35,920
Do you really know what he's thinking?

843
01:06:37,960 --> 01:06:39,240
See? No freaking way you do.

844
01:06:40,400 --> 01:06:42,800
Listen and think. What comes after that?

845
01:06:43,360 --> 01:06:44,960
Think, think, think.

846
01:06:45,040 --> 01:06:47,400
Think and execute!

847
01:06:48,240 --> 01:06:50,560
What about savory dishes?
What do you like?

848
01:06:50,640 --> 01:06:53,360
I eat garlic shrimp a lot.

849
01:06:54,840 --> 01:06:58,480
Do you know that Duang
asked me to teach him how to make that?

850
01:06:58,560 --> 01:07:02,240
Dad and Funan had to eat shrimp
for a week before he got it right.

851
01:07:02,320 --> 01:07:03,800
So, did you get to taste it?

852
01:07:03,880 --> 01:07:04,720
Was it any good?

853
01:07:05,320 --> 01:07:06,640
I did. It was pretty good.

854
01:07:07,440 --> 01:07:08,960
That's nice to hear.

855
01:07:09,040 --> 01:07:12,080
But do you know that
Duang isn't very talented?

856
01:07:12,160 --> 01:07:16,520
I sent him to every class out there.
Whatever he wanted to attend, I sent him.

857
01:07:16,600 --> 01:07:18,560
Like when Duang
asked to take guitar classes,

858
01:07:18,640 --> 01:07:19,800
I allowed him to.

859
01:07:19,880 --> 01:07:21,800
But after a while,
he said it hurt his hands.

860
01:07:21,880 --> 01:07:24,720
What did he do?
He quit since it hurt, right?

861
01:07:24,800 --> 01:07:28,680
After that, he was picked on,
so he wanted to do taekwondo.

862
01:07:28,760 --> 01:07:31,800
I bought him the uniform
and got him geared up.

863
01:07:31,880 --> 01:07:33,360
I got him all the belts out there.

864
01:07:33,440 --> 01:07:36,480
Then he got hurt,
so there goes another class.

865
01:07:36,560 --> 01:07:38,280
But I didn't give up.

866
01:07:38,360 --> 01:07:40,840
After a while, he asked me
to take drawing classes.

867
01:07:40,920 --> 01:07:42,440
That's when I felt uneasy

868
01:07:42,520 --> 01:07:44,880
since it required him
to concentrate and stay still.

869
01:07:44,960 --> 01:07:46,840
I thought, "Gosh, he's not gonna last."

870
01:07:46,920 --> 01:07:48,920
But in the end, he did!

871
01:07:49,000 --> 01:07:50,600
I was over the moon, Qin.

872
01:07:50,680 --> 01:07:52,680
This is what's right for him.

873
01:07:54,360 --> 01:07:56,760
And I think you are too.

874
01:07:59,320 --> 01:08:01,280
He really tried,

875
01:08:01,360 --> 01:08:04,120
whether it was the show or the cooking.

876
01:08:09,320 --> 01:08:10,800
I'm his mom, after all.

877
01:08:13,520 --> 01:08:15,320
But I thank you

878
01:08:16,279 --> 01:08:18,240
for being in his life.

879
01:08:19,080 --> 01:08:22,479
There's no need to thank me, Mom.
You've raised him well.

880
01:08:23,040 --> 01:08:25,399
That's why he turned out to be so lovable.

881
01:08:26,520 --> 01:08:27,439
Besides…

882
01:08:29,520 --> 01:08:31,120
I didn't choose him.

883
01:08:31,200 --> 01:08:32,560
He chose me.

884
01:08:38,120 --> 01:08:40,920
I understand why he chose you, Qin.

885
01:08:46,279 --> 01:08:49,040
Jeez, my voice is starting to get shaky.

886
01:08:49,120 --> 01:08:51,479
Let's turn on the stove
and make jelly, Qin.

887
01:08:57,640 --> 01:08:58,560
Here.

888
01:08:58,640 --> 01:08:59,600
This is yours.

889
01:09:00,359 --> 01:09:01,800
Betong chicken.

890
01:09:04,160 --> 01:09:06,319
- Qin.
- Yes?

891
01:09:06,399 --> 01:09:08,160
Eat as much as you can.

892
01:09:08,240 --> 01:09:12,319
Mom's Betong chicken
is the best in the entire world.

893
01:09:12,399 --> 01:09:16,120
That's right. I worked so hard on it.
The meat is gonna be so tender.

894
01:09:16,640 --> 01:09:17,479
Okay.

895
01:09:20,240 --> 01:09:21,920
Quiet down. It's embarrassing!

896
01:09:23,640 --> 01:09:24,479
Qin.

897
01:09:26,279 --> 01:09:27,479
Want to spend the night?

898
01:09:29,560 --> 01:09:30,479
Spend the night?

899
01:09:40,240 --> 01:09:43,880
Since you drove a long way,
just spend the night here, alright?

900
01:09:44,479 --> 01:09:46,240
- True.
- Honey!

901
01:09:48,600 --> 01:09:49,439
That's right.

902
01:09:50,720 --> 01:09:52,040
Tonight,

903
01:09:52,120 --> 01:09:53,600
stay over, would you?

904
01:09:55,520 --> 01:09:57,000
Just stay the night.

905
01:09:57,080 --> 01:09:59,080
I have so much to gossip about.

906
01:09:59,160 --> 01:10:01,120
Also, I checked the weather.

907
01:10:01,200 --> 01:10:04,680
It's going to rain cats and dogs.
I'll be worried if you're on the road.

908
01:10:04,760 --> 01:10:06,560
- Whoa.
- Whoa, really?!

909
01:10:06,640 --> 01:10:09,840
- That's dangerous.
- Couldn't be more dangerous, Mom!

910
01:10:09,920 --> 01:10:11,640
No, that's dangerous.

911
01:10:11,720 --> 01:10:12,680
Seriously!

912
01:10:13,520 --> 01:10:14,800
I don't agree.

913
01:10:15,320 --> 01:10:17,320
- Or spend half the night.
- Let's eat first.

914
01:10:17,840 --> 01:10:19,000
Please stay over.

915
01:10:19,080 --> 01:10:20,960
- Alright, thank you.
- Yes.

916
01:10:22,560 --> 01:10:26,040
It's too dangerous on the road.
What if there's an accident?

917
01:10:26,120 --> 01:10:29,520
Yeah, it's better this way.
So we don't have to worry.

918
01:10:29,600 --> 01:10:30,680
- Exactly.
- So…

919
01:10:30,760 --> 01:10:32,440
Do you have class tomorrow?

920
01:10:32,920 --> 01:10:33,760
I do.

921
01:10:35,880 --> 01:10:36,800
In the afternoon.

922
01:10:39,280 --> 01:10:40,480
Me too.

923
01:10:41,160 --> 01:10:42,680
So you can go back tomorrow morning.

924
01:10:44,280 --> 01:10:45,720
Yes, tomorrow morning.

925
01:10:45,800 --> 01:10:48,320
So, Qin will stay in Duang's room then.

926
01:10:49,240 --> 01:10:50,080
What?!

927
01:10:50,160 --> 01:10:51,720
Of course he will!

928
01:10:51,800 --> 01:10:56,560
Huh? Why are you screaming at me?
Obviously, Qin will stay in your room.

929
01:10:56,640 --> 01:10:58,320
He can't sleep in my room.

930
01:10:58,400 --> 01:11:00,200
Why would he stay in your room?

931
01:11:00,280 --> 01:11:01,560
He won't!

932
01:11:01,640 --> 01:11:03,680
He will be in your room!

933
01:11:03,760 --> 01:11:06,160
Do you have to keep raising your voice?

934
01:11:06,240 --> 01:11:09,200
He will be in your room.
I've already cleaned it!

935
01:11:09,280 --> 01:11:11,960
Alright. It's settled then.

936
01:11:12,720 --> 01:11:13,560
Qin,

937
01:11:14,120 --> 01:11:16,000
- you'll sleep in Duang's room.
- End of story.

938
01:11:16,080 --> 01:11:17,640
- Yeah, that's it.
- Alright.

939
01:11:31,240 --> 01:11:32,800
It's way cleaner than your condo.

940
01:11:34,200 --> 01:11:35,200
Definitely.

941
01:11:35,920 --> 01:11:38,240
Mom is a clean freak.

942
01:11:39,200 --> 01:11:40,920
I can tell. Your house is very tidy.

943
01:11:56,640 --> 01:11:58,560
This was from
when I took taekwondo classes.

944
01:11:59,120 --> 01:12:00,640
I lasted three days before I quit.

945
01:12:01,840 --> 01:12:02,920
Your mom already told me.

946
01:12:03,640 --> 01:12:04,560
Whoa,

947
01:12:05,320 --> 01:12:07,680
she gossiped about me?

948
01:12:08,840 --> 01:12:11,000
But I want to know more. Tell me.

949
01:12:11,640 --> 01:12:12,800
When I was small,

950
01:12:12,880 --> 01:12:14,840
Mom had me do a lot of things,

951
01:12:14,920 --> 01:12:17,040
but I was never good at anything.

952
01:12:17,120 --> 01:12:20,680
Luckily, she told me to tell her
if I didn't come to like it.

953
01:12:21,480 --> 01:12:23,080
Mom said,

954
01:12:23,160 --> 01:12:27,960
"Don't be afraid to fail
if you're eager to get back on your feet."

955
01:12:28,520 --> 01:12:31,440
She's such an angel.
I really like your family.

956
01:12:32,800 --> 01:12:33,800
That's how I found out

957
01:12:34,400 --> 01:12:36,520
I like drawing the most.

958
01:12:36,600 --> 01:12:37,480
But now,

959
01:12:38,600 --> 01:12:40,760
I like you even more!

960
01:12:52,560 --> 01:12:53,480
Stop it.

961
01:12:56,280 --> 01:12:57,560
Duang!

962
01:13:05,920 --> 01:13:06,880
That's a cute picture.

963
01:13:08,160 --> 01:13:11,760
Jeez… Let's take a shower
if you're gonna compliment me this much.

964
01:13:12,320 --> 01:13:13,400
Too dangerous.

965
01:13:13,480 --> 01:13:16,640
Are you crazy? I won't do anything
unless you allow me to.

966
01:13:16,720 --> 01:13:17,720
Is that so?

967
01:13:17,800 --> 01:13:19,280
You always go for it.

968
01:13:19,360 --> 01:13:20,560
That's nuts!

969
01:13:28,200 --> 01:13:30,160
Here. These pajamas are for you.

970
01:13:30,240 --> 01:13:31,600
No need for underwear.

971
01:13:31,720 --> 01:13:33,160
I'll wash your clothes.

972
01:13:35,280 --> 01:13:36,360
Your dirty mind again.

973
01:13:36,440 --> 01:13:37,800
You brought it up.

974
01:13:37,880 --> 01:13:39,800
I was just mentioning it.

975
01:13:40,520 --> 01:13:41,760
Let's take a shower together.

976
01:13:42,360 --> 01:13:43,680
Save the planet.

977
01:13:46,720 --> 01:13:47,960
Are you giving in?

978
01:13:48,880 --> 01:13:50,280
Or do I need to do more?

979
01:13:54,480 --> 01:13:56,840
If I shower with you,
then we're going straight to sleep.

980
01:13:56,920 --> 01:13:58,360
No more touchy feely.

981
01:13:59,280 --> 01:14:00,200
You got it.

982
01:14:07,960 --> 01:14:10,600
Get me a towel. I don't have one.

983
01:15:12,080 --> 01:15:13,040
You're all mine.

984
01:15:54,560 --> 01:15:55,600
Duang…

985
01:15:55,680 --> 01:15:56,640
Don't bite.

986
01:16:07,920 --> 01:16:08,880
Just a little taste.

987
01:16:24,040 --> 01:16:25,280
I can't stand it anymore.

988
01:16:29,360 --> 01:16:30,480
You're just…

989
01:16:30,560 --> 01:16:31,960
Please?

990
01:17:04,440 --> 01:17:06,120
Roar.

991
01:17:06,880 --> 01:17:07,720
Go get 'em.

992
01:17:51,920 --> 01:17:52,840
Duang.

993
01:17:53,520 --> 01:17:55,000
Be gentle.

994
01:18:13,600 --> 01:18:14,520
Do you like it?

995
01:18:46,320 --> 01:18:47,240
Are you ready?

996
01:18:47,720 --> 01:18:49,480
Yes.

997
01:18:49,560 --> 01:18:50,400
I am.

998
01:20:11,320 --> 01:20:13,160
<i>It's confusing</i>
<i>that we had to come to Japan,</i>

999
01:20:13,240 --> 01:20:16,040
<i>- but I think the timing is just perfect.</i>
<i>- What do you mean?</i>

1000
01:20:16,600 --> 01:20:19,160
Perfect for our honeymoon of course.

1001
01:20:20,680 --> 01:20:22,200
Today is our monthiversary again.

1002
01:20:22,280 --> 01:20:24,240
I want this trip to be a gift for you.

1003
01:20:24,320 --> 01:20:27,560
What's the difference between
being into someone and liking them?

1004
01:20:27,640 --> 01:20:28,920
Excuse me.

1005
01:20:29,000 --> 01:20:31,720
I wanna sing the song I wrote for Duang.

1006
01:20:32,320 --> 01:20:33,200
Duang,

1007
01:20:34,120 --> 01:20:35,240
I wrote this song for you.
